==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hugjan'' ‘think, consider’.  Cognate with Gothic [[𐌷𐌿𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽]], Old Norse [[huga]] (Icelandic [[hugsa]] ‘to think’).  Related to Middle Scots [[huik]] ‘regard, consider’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hyʤan/

===Verb===
